# Cursor Rules for Naafe Project

## Project Context
This is an Arabic service marketplace platform for Egypt. All development must follow the documentation in `naafe-docs/` directory.

## Critical Constraints
- ONLY use shadcn/ui components - no other UI libraries
- Stripe test mode only - no production payment integration
- Egypt-specific adaptations required (Arabic support, local payments, elderly-friendly)
- WCAG 2.2 AA compliance mandatory
- Mobile-first responsive design with large buttons

## Documentation References
- Theme System: `naafe-docs/THEME_SYSTEM.md`
- Technical Architecture: `naafe-docs/TECHNICAL_ARCHITECTURE.md`
- Business Logic: `naafe-docs/BUSINESS_LOGIC.md`
- Development Roadmap: `naafe-docs/DEVELOPMENT_ROADMAP.md`
- Project Overview: `naafe-docs/PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md`

## Development Guidelines
- Follow the current development phase from DEVELOPMENT_ROADMAP.md
- Use theme colors from THEME_SYSTEM.md (Teal, Orange, Purple)
- Implement Egypt-specific features from BUSINESS_LOGIC.md
- Follow database schema from TECHNICAL_ARCHITECTURE.md
- Ensure all components are accessible and mobile-friendly

## Code Standards
- TypeScript strict mode
- Functional components with hooks
- Proper error handling
- Loading states for all async operations
- Comprehensive accessibility attributes

## Before Implementing Any Feature
1. Check which development phase it belongs to
2. Reference the specific requirements from naafe-docs/
3. Confirm shadcn/ui component usage
4. Include Egypt-specific adaptations
5. Ensure accessibility compliance

## Quality Checks
- Run `npx tsc --noEmit` before committing
- Verify all components use shadcn/ui
- Check theme color usage
- Confirm Egypt-specific features
- Validate against current development phase
